    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-12-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-12-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="278"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d278">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.002/67: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-12-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 27, 1921</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received 8:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>468. New Cabinet assumed office 25th: Premier, Liang Shih-yi; Foreign Affairs,
                    Yen; Finance, Chang Hu; War, Pao Kwei-ching; Navy, Li Ting-hsin; Communications,
                    Yeh Kung-cho; Justice, Wang Chung-hui; Commerce, Chi Yao-shan; Interior, Kao
                    Ling-wei; Education, Huang Yen-pei.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schurman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
